Today, I will share some of my tips to develop WordPress Plugins which can cope with your Wordpress Themes & Other Wordpress Plugin:

[huge_it_share]

<h4>Tip 01: Use a strategy to Develop Wordpress Plugin</h4>
Yes you have to plan to develop any Wordpress Plugin properly. Try to checklist below points:
<ul>	
<li>Is this plugin for fun or demonstration purposes for real world.</li>
<li>Check is there similar plugins already been written? Check the <a href="http://wordpress.org/extend/plugins/" target="_blank" rel="nofollow"> Wordpress Plugin Repository</a>.</li>
<li>Can you provide support to users for your plugin.</li>
</ul>

This all points are important, because it shows how dedicated you are towards the development of Wordpress Plugin.

<hr>

<h4>Tip 02: Use Clean &amp; Neat coding method</h4>
Simple things like consistent spacing, indenting, informative variable naming and comments are a good place to start. That's the only difference between best developers and good developers. WordPress provides has an  guide to coding standards. If you code to a standard your code will be easier to understand, edit and debug.

Below is sample of how to write you code clean &amp; neat:

<pre rel="WORDPRESS"><code data-lang="wordpress">class my_class{
  function hello_world(){
    return 'Learn Wordpress';
  }
  function goodbye_world(){
   return 'Develop Plugin';
  }
}</code></pre>

